1. Student recruitment activities

Participate and coordinate recruitment events, including VGU campus tours, open days, high-school visits, career fairs, and online information sessions;
Provide accurate and timely advice to prospective students on admissions processes, program offerings, and scholarship information;
Build and maintain relationships with schools, community organizations, and other external partners to enhance recruitment pipelines;
Collaborate with the marketing team to develop promotional materials and campaigns tailored to target audiences.
2. Reporting and analysis

Prepare detailed reports on recruitment activities, including event outcomes, attendance metrics, and conversion rates;
Conduct market analysis to identify trends and opportunities for student recruitment, particularly in STEM fields;
Evaluate the effectiveness of recruitment strategies and provide data-driven recommendations to meet VGU's enrollment goals.
3. Other duties

Attending events as required out of normal office hours;
Occasional weekend work (a day in lieu will be implemented);
Occasional travel to other areas across Vietnam for up to 5 days.

