Position Overview
This position is fully responsible for the two major functions of the group's environment, health and safety (EHS) and corporate social responsibility (CSR), leading the formulation and implementation of relevant strategies and policies to improve the group's compliance level and sustainable development capabilities. This position requires a strong strategic vision and implementation capabilities, and coordinates the management of EHS and CSR work at the group headquarters and various production bases to ensure that the company meets the requirements of relevant laws and regulations and customer review standards during rapid expansion and IPO preparation.

Main Responsibilities:
1. Strategy and policy formulation
• Responsible for formulating the group's medium- and long-term development strategies and annual plans for EHS and CSR;
• Establish and continuously optimize the group's unified EHS and CSR management policies and implementation standards;
• Assess the group's risks in the areas of environment, safety, occupational health and social responsibility, and propose improvement suggestions and action plans.
2. Functional team management
• Directly lead the group's EHS manager and CSR manager to promote team capacity building and professional improvement;
• Coordinate the guidance, supervision and support of related work of each factory to ensure consistency in standard implementation;
• Lead cross-regional EHS and CSR work meetings and reporting mechanisms to promote experience sharing and problem closure.
3. CSR audit and customer management
• Gradually taking over the core tasks of CSR audit preparation, certification application, customer communication and audit response from CTIC Consulting Company;
• During the three-year transition period, work with CTIC to develop a knowledge transfer plan and gradually achieve internal leadership;
• Establish and maintain official communication mechanisms and relationship networks with customers, audit agencies, and certification organizations.
4. Training and cultural construction
• Promote the construction of the group's EHS and CSR culture;
• Organize relevant training to enhance the sense of responsibility and practical ability of management and grassroots employees.
5. Monitoring and reporting
• Establish key performance indicators (KPIs) and audit tracking systems;
• Regularly report to management on the Group’s EHS and CSR work progress, issues and suggestions;
• Cooperate in the preparation of the group's annual CSR report and support brand and investor communication needs.

Key Performance Indicator (KPI) Examples
• The approval rate of the group and each factory customer (first time/re-examination)
• Annual work injury rate/number of major environmental incidents
• The reduction in consulting fees and the improvement in the independent response capabilities of the internal team
• CSR system internal control integrity and gap rectification completion rate
• EHS/CSR training coverage and effect evaluation results

Job Requirements:
Educational Background:
• Bachelor degree or above, major in environmental engineering, safety management, corporate social responsibility, sustainable development, etc. is preferred; with CSR and EHS related certifications ( ISO14001, ISO45001, etc.) will be given priority.
• Registered Safety Engineer or equivalent certification

Work Experience:
• At least 10 years of relevant working experience in cross-regional manufacturing industry;
• At least 5 years of EHS or CSR functional management experience, with the ability to lead a team/cross-department coordination;
• Familiar with customer review process and mainstream CSR certification system, and has led key customer or third-party audits.
Ability requirements:
• Possess strategic thinking and system planning capabilities, and be able to coordinate multi-country/multi-factory management from an organizational level;
• Excellent communication and coordination skills, able to effectively interface with third parties, customers and different levels of the internal organization;
• Fluent in both Chinese and English, able to handle communications and written reports for international clients or organizations.
• Expert in office application software, ERP system and EHS&CSR reporting software or platform

